Notice The Nurses: LILLIAN D. WALD

Lillian D. Wald was the pioneering force behind the practice of community nursing. 

After working with struggling families in New York’s Lower East Side, she started the Visiting Nursing Service of New York to bring affordable healthcare to the neighborhood. 

From there, she dedicated her life to activism, campaigning for women’s suffrage, and supporting racial integration. 

She also co-founded the Henry Street Settlement, a non-profit organization that continues to provide social services, arts programs, and healthcare to New Yorkers of all ages to this day. 

#NoticeTheNurses #WomensHistoryMonth
